  "subject": "Fix RTD build: pin setuptools<81 and sphinx<9",
  "commit_message": "Fix RTD build: pin setuptools<81 and sphinx<9\n\nThe Read the Docs build environment runs 'pip install --upgrade setuptools'\nbefore processing requirements-docs.txt, which installs setuptools 82.0.1.\nsetuptools>=82 removed pkg_resources, which sphinxcontrib-needs 0.7.9 imports\nat load time (via sphinxcontrib.needs.logging).\n\nUnlike the GHA CI tox environment, RTD does not use the ONAP\nupper-constraints file that pins setuptools==69.0.3, so the upper bound\nmust be specified directly in requirements-docs.txt.\n\nAlso pin sphinx<9 since sphinxcontrib-needs 0.7.9 has not been tested\nwith Sphinx 9.x and RTD's pre-install step upgrades Sphinx to the latest\nversion (9.1.0) before processing requirements.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: I1e1b3d36ee19703ac696c7edac4d5a8deec03679\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
